  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
        <div xml:id="KT157-kilavi">
          <p type="edition">pūppeytiya talaimakaḷ uraittatu.</p>
          <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">Told by HER who had reached her (monthly) menstruation.</p>
          </div>


        <div xml:id="KT157">
            <lg type="edition">
<l>                kukkū veṉṟatu kōḻi yataṉetir</l>
<l>                tuṭkeṉ ṟaṉṟeṉ ṟūya neñcan</l>
<l>                tōṭōy kātalarp pirikkum</l>
<l>                vāḷpōl vaikaṟai vantaṉṟā leṉavē.</l>
             </lg>
            <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
           <l>“Kukkū” said the cock.</l>
           <l rend="indent3">At that</l>
           <l>my pure heart stopped beating:<note place="foot">There is a second way to split the sandhi here, namely as <term xml:lang="ta">tuṭku eṉṟu aṉṟu</term>: "my pure heart did not say <term xml:lang="ta">tuṭku</term> [anymore]".</note></l>
           <l rend="indent">To separate [me] from the lover at my shoulder</l>
           <l>just like a sword dawn has come,</l>
           <l rend="indent4">says he.</l>

            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
